the Markov Model interested#NewlineIn probability theory#Comma a Markov model is a enables reasoning and computation with the model that would otherwise be very difficult. The simplest Markov model is the Markov chain. It models the state of a system with a random variable that changes through time.

A hidden Markov model is a statistical model in which the system being modeled is assumed to be a chain of unobserved (or hidden) states. Hidden Markov models are used applications such as speech recognition#Comma handwriting analysis#Comma gesture recognition#Comma part-of-speech tagging#Comma musical score following and bioinformatics.
